1
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:05,589
[Growls]

2
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,757
[Dolphins chatter]

3
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:11,553
[Screeches]

4
00:00:13,305 --> 00:00:14,431
J Adventure time J

5
00:00:14,431 --> 00:00:15,682
J Come on, grab your friends &

6
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:18,519
> We'll go
to very distant lands 7

7
00:00:18,602 --> 00:00:20,896
J With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong J

8
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:22,523
J And possibly BMO 7

9
00:00:22,606 --> 00:00:24,399
J It's adventure time 7

10
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:36,078
Susan? I mean, Kara?

11
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:37,704
Seems like you're leading us
somewhere.

12
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,790
We're taking a ship
to Founders Island,

13
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:42,084
because judging by the state
of these facilities...

14
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:45,796
...Hub Island has been abandoned
for over a decade.

15
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:48,173
Dang, I missed big words.

16
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:51,093
This island is where I trained
to be a Seeker.

17
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:57,474
So, wait, why are we going
to Founders Island?

18
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,435
I'm taking you back to your mom.

19
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,187
BMO, would you talk
to this console?

20
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:04,523
I can't access it
without my implant.

21
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:07,067
Um...you knew my mom?

22
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,694
You're gonna just drop that?!

23
00:01:08,819 --> 00:01:10,904
Her name is Minerva.

24
00:01:10,946 --> 00:01:12,823
- She's a Helper.
-[Ding]

25
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:13,949
Oh, thanks, BMO.

26
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,660
Now let's try
and start this sucker.

27
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:19,830
[Horn honks]

28
00:01:19,830 --> 00:01:22,833
What's happening?
Are we being arrested?

29
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,460
Don't worry, ladies. I'll get
you to your senior swim class.

30
00:01:25,544 --> 00:01:28,088
TOGETHER:
Thank you, Dr. Minnie.

31
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,590
- Oh!
- Whoa!

32
00:01:30,424 --> 00:01:31,174
[Gasps]

33
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:32,968
[Tires screech]

34
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:37,806
[Muffled voice] Hey,
it's not a crosswalk, ya know!

35
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:40,225
It's -- It's not a...
[Groans]

36
00:01:50,569 --> 00:01:52,237
MAN: The end.

37
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:54,990
You have been listening
to "Wizards Way."

38
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:03,832
So I hear you guys wanna do
some explorin"?

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,460
Canteens. Cool.

40
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,170
So what do you got for me?

41
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,381
Credits?
I don't take credits.

42
00:02:11,423 --> 00:02:13,300
I want gadgets.

43
00:02:13,425 --> 00:02:16,678
See this gum?
It used to be a book on tape.

44
00:02:16,762 --> 00:02:18,555
Gadgets.

45
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:20,057
Hmm.

46
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,267
[Whirring]

47
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:24,936
[Gasps coughs]

48
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:27,439
Hey, not bad.

49
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:28,565
I'll take it.

50
00:02:29,441 --> 00:02:31,068
Get down to Basket Beach,

51
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:33,820
and I'll meet you at the boat
in 30 minutes.

52
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,826
-[Beep]
- Hey, there.

53
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:43,455
Uh, you got a couple of Hiders
headed for Basket Beach.

54
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:44,790
You're welcome. Bye.

55
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:48,919
Yah!

56
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,837
You startled me.
[Laughs]

57
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:53,840
We understand that you can
get us past the Seekers.

58
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:56,927
Yeah, but you just missed
today's boat.

59
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,721
We understand
that you like gadgets?

60
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:01,807
I do like them.

61
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,310
[Click]

62
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:09,481
Hello. Hello. Hello.

63
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:11,983
I don't like it.
I love it!

64
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:15,320
Tell ya what, get yourself
down to Basket Beach ASAP.

65
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,364
You're not coming with us?

66
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:19,825
Once I determine
you haven't been followed,

67
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:21,868
I will join you at the boat.

68
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,746
We insist you join us now.

69
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:29,584
Let's go to the beach.

70
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:31,628
DR. GROSS: Bring back
those Hiders, y'all!

71
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:34,631
[Alarm blaring]

72
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:37,134
Aah!

73
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,763
What do you got for me, Kara?

74
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:44,474
A sad ol' Hider
with two busted legs.

75
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:46,768
Oh, I love busted legs!

76
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:48,145
[Groans]

77
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:50,355
When will he be at full health?

78
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:51,273
Tomorrow morning.

79
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:54,025
Okay, I'll have a transport
here in the morning

80
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,902
to shuttle him to re-ed.

81
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,406
Re-education.

82
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,787
Oh, you're awake.

83
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:08,039
We set both your legs.
They were broken.

84
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,792
Other than that, you only have
psychological problems.

85
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:13,044
Well, I could've told you that.

86
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:15,672
- You don't look like a Hider.
- I'm not.

87
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:19,092
It was a wrong place,
wrong time type of deal.

88
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:22,262
It's true!
I love it here!

89
00:04:22,888 --> 00:04:24,473
So. . .white hat.

90
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,767
- You're a Helper, huh?
- Yes.

91
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:30,145
I think that fella's
still alive.

92
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:35,108
Hello. Hello. Hello.

93
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:36,359
Very funny.

94
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:39,112
If I don't see you before
tomorrow, enjoy re-education.

95
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:42,032
- You're leavin?
- I have things to do.

96
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,658
What am I gonna look at
when you leave?

97
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:47,037
Leave some flowers or somethin'!

98
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,125
These are in the trash?

99
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:54,669
- I think someone died.
- Oh, that's great!

100
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:00,926
You're trying to escape?

101
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:02,385
No! I'm --

102
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:04,179
Wrong place, wrong time?

103
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:06,807
No, no. I have to, uh...

104
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:08,141
- [crunch]
- Aah!

105
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:09,142
Aah!

106
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:10,435
- [Clank]
- Uhh!

107
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,812
Aah!

108
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,065
This is kind of a setback.

109
00:05:15,065 --> 00:05:17,692
But nothing
a good night's sleep can't fix.

110
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:21,446
You're not sleeping tonight.
You've got a serious concussion.

111
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:23,073
- And I'm not sleeping tonight...
- [Click]

112
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,325
...because apparently you need
a babysitter.

113
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:28,578
- I'm not a baby.
- Okay.

114
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,412
Aah!

115
00:05:29,538 --> 00:05:31,081
Keep those elevated.

116
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:35,210
I have to figure out a new
lineup for the JV curling team.

117
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,712
You wanna sign my cast?

118
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:39,214
Which one?

119
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:42,050
[Chuckles]
You're all right, Doc.

120
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:44,594
Hey, you know I'm not going
to re-ed tomorrow, right?

121
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:46,054
Oh, yeah?

122
00:05:46,096 --> 00:05:48,348
I'll tell 'em this was
just a misunderstanding,

123
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:51,852
and then I'll glide out
the front door a free man.

124
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:54,980
Free to have dinner...with you?

125
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:56,231
If you wanted to.

126
00:05:56,356 --> 00:05:58,733
I mean, I-I want to.

127
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:05,365
So what are you,
a con artist or something?

128
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,701
Yeah, you make it sound
so glamorous.

129
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:10,745
How about me?
How would you con me?

130
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:13,748
I wouldn't con you.
I wanna have dinner with you.

131
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:15,083
[Laughs]

132
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:18,753
Okay, but if you had to,
how would you do it?

133
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:21,882
Um, okay, you like
helping people, right?

134
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,593
So I'd get you
to feel sorry for me.

135
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,636
I'd act real pitiful.

136
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,263
I don't think that would work.

137
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,765
I mean, you're number one
at number two, after all.

138
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,225
-[Laughing]
-[Laughs]

139
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:34,519
You saw my underwear!
You're -- [Laughs]

140
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:37,272
MINERVA: Oh!
- MARTIN: You're all right, Doc.

141
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,276
[Pounding on door]

142
00:06:41,276 --> 00:06:42,152
SEEKER:
Open up!

143
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:44,029
Sure thing.
Just a --

144
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,032
Give me a boost, Doc!

145
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:48,408
[Door clanks]

146
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:50,160
Oh, uh, hello, Dr. Campbell.

147
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:53,288
Prepare for re-education,
Mertens!

148
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,789
You got the wrong man, fella.

149
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:58,043
I've been helping beefcakes like
you catch Hiders for months.

150
00:06:58,043 --> 00:07:00,045
We know you've been playing
both sides.

151
00:07:00,045 --> 00:07:01,379
You think that's not hurtful?

152
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:04,049
Uh-oh. That was kind of
my only plan.

153
00:07:04,049 --> 00:07:05,550
[Sobbing]

154
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,304
You finally ran out of quarters,
didn't you, Marty?

155
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,014
[Sobbing]

156
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:12,641
Poor little Marty!

157
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,309
[Sobbing continues]

158
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,312
MINERVA:
Hold up, guys!

159
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:19,439
Hey, I'm so sorry about this,

160
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,650
but I was completing
checkout forms for Mr. Mertens,

161
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:24,444
and it turns out
he's medically unfit for re-ed.

162
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,655
He's got a rare condition
called garbage body.

163
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:29,324
Uh, that sounds completely fake

164
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:31,409
coming from anybody but you,
Dr. Campbell!

165
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:32,410
[Laughs]

166
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,912
See you at the Fun Run!

167
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,665
That was breathtaking
con work, Doc.

168
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:39,334
So you gonna buy me dinner
or what?

169
00:07:39,334 --> 00:07:41,795
J I heard that you loved me J

170
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:44,339
J But only for two weeks J

171
00:07:44,422 --> 00:07:46,716
J To be hopeless or not to be [

172
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,718
s I'm weak with indecision J

173
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,720
J Could we begin again 7

174
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:53,598
J On a terrible date 7

175
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:57,978
J It would be
greatly appreciated by me 7

176
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:02,983
J I'll wear my normal shoes
this time &

177
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:06,069
J Then maybe you'd like me 7

178
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:08,238
J Better in the sunlight &

179
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:10,240
J If I built a raft &

180
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,993
> Will you stay with me then 7

181
00:08:13,076 --> 00:08:17,205
J And fall in love
all over again? J

182
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:19,249
MINERVA:
Oh, I'm so late!

183
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,251
[Cooing]

184
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:24,129
I'll be home by 7:00.
Mwah!

185
00:08:24,129 --> 00:08:25,463
Hey, can you run a load
of laundry?

186
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,965
You got it.

187
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,383
Should I order us
something for --

188
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:30,260
Veggie thali and a mango lassi!

189
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,886
[Tires screech]

190
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,430
[Crickets chirp]

191
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:36,391
[Laughs]
Yeah, that's Mr. Bear.

192
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,934
Pretty interesting guy, huh?

193
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:41,187
Where the heck is
Mommy's Indian food, huh?

194
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:43,148
[Laughs]
Hey, look what you got.

195
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:46,526
That's one of my old gadgets,
the breadstick wand.

196
00:08:46,568 --> 00:08:47,902
-[Crying]
-[Running footsteps]

197
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:50,572
- That must be the grub.
-[Growls]

198
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:52,657
End of the line, Mertens!

199
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:54,576
We're here for vengeance!

200
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:56,161
- [Chirps]
- Ha!

201
00:08:56,286 --> 00:08:58,163
J Hot breadsticks is
what we bake 7

202
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:00,832
; We don't bake pie
and we don't bake cake 7

203
00:09:00,832 --> 00:09:03,418
- & Breadsticks... &
- You pathetic man.

204
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:05,211
Uhh!

205
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:11,217
Don't worry. Daddy's got a raft
stashed around here somewhere.

206
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:12,969
-[Door opens]
- MINERVA: Hey, guys!

207
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:14,971
-[Light switch clicks]
- I'm ready for that thali --

208
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:16,973
Martin?

209
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:18,475
Finn!

210
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,810
[Growls]

211
00:09:20,852 --> 00:09:23,229
Mertens!

212
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:25,440
Phew!

213
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:26,983
Let's give Mom a text.

214
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:30,737
Yeah, I guess we'll just circle
around the island and see if --

215
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:33,114
[Thunder crashes]

216
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,200
-[Crying]
Freaking Back to Nature Island!

217
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,203
Let's -- Let's just wait out
the storm, and then...

218
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,580
Aah! The Guardian!

219
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:42,749
No, I'm not trying to leave!

220
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:46,461
-[Crying]
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

221
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,755
Don't worry.
Daddy's always got a plan.

222
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:51,508
[Lights clank]

223
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:54,594
- Finn, I'll be back for you.
-[Ding]

224
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,144
Here comes the rascal!

225
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:04,979
Oop! Wait, wait. Wait! Uh-oh.

226
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:06,731
Aah!

227
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:08,483
- [Thud]
- Uhh!

228
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,777
[Glass shatters]

229
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:13,530
-[Beeping]
- Hello. Hello.

230
00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:14,739
Hello.

231
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,668
J Hot breadsticks
is what we bake J

232
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,170
; We don't bake pie
and we don't bake cake 7

233
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:31,923
I can't believe that of all
the hundreds that have tried,

234
00:10:32,048 --> 00:10:34,801
the gallbag that finally
makes it past the Guardian

235
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:37,428
is Martin Mertens!

236
00:10:40,682 --> 00:10:42,392
[Voice breaks]
I don't understand.

237
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,525
[Whirring]

238
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,070
- [Thud]
- Aaayyy!

239
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:57,198
[Whirring]

240
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:00,702
Hey.

241
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:02,078
Oh. Hey, what's up?

242
00:11:02,162 --> 00:11:05,165
Nothing. I just haven't
said anything in a while.

243
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,555
This party is so crazy!

